  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Accessibility features help a wide range of people interact with their devices. For many, accessibility is a necessity. For others, itâ€™s a practicality. For example, closed captions can be necessary for someone who is deaf or hard of hearing, but also useful for someone watching a video in a noisy environment."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Whether youâ€™re developing a new app, or updating an existing one, consider the needs of all the people who may use your app. People can personalize their devices by choosing which accessibility features give them the best user experience."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "By designing your app with accessibility in mind, you make it possible for everyone to enjoy your app. For simplicity, there are four accessibility domains to keep in mind when thinking about your users:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "unorderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Vision â€” A person may be blind or color blind, or have a vision challenge that makes focusing difficult."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Hearing â€” A person may be deaf, have partial hearing loss, or have difficulty hearing sounds within a certain range."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Physical and motor skills â€” A person with reduced mobility may have difficulty holding a device or tapping the interface."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Learning and literacy â€” A person may have difficulty remembering a sequence of steps, or they may find an overly complex user interface difficult to process and manage."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Your app can tap into macOS accessibility features, like VoiceOver, simply by using standard AppKit controls."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Users can choose between automatic accessibility and the native accessibility of the app, based on user preference. By default, the native accessibility of the app is preferred.Â But if no accessibility is implemented in the app, automatic accessibility is applied."
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "style": "note",
          "name": "Note"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        }
      ]
    }
